The commission resumed its work on Tuesday with an application to summons Zuma. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Commission Inquiry resumes on Wednesday with evidence from retired Col Johannes Van Loggerenberg. He is a former member of the now disbanded Scorpions crime busting unit. The commission resumed its work on Tuesday with an application to summons Zuma. Former president Jacob Zuma's lawyers told the commission he's not well enough to appear before the commission of inquiry into state capture. Judge Raymond Zondo has reluctantly accepted an offer by Zuma's legal team to meet with his medical staff.